s of Alberto Caeiro | others = Chris Daniels, transl | place = Exeter, UK | publisher = Shearsman Books | year = 2007 | isbn = 978-1-905700-24-0 | url = http://www.shearsman.com/pages/books/catalog/2007/pessoa_caeiro.html | access-date = 28 July 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110404053758/http://www.shearsman.com/pages/books/catalog/2007/pessoa_caeiro.html | archive-date = 4 April 2011 | url-status = dead | df = dmy-all }}\n* {{citation | title = Selected English Poems | place = Exeter, UK | publisher = Shearsman Books | year = 2007 | isbn = 978-1-905700-26-4 | url = http://www.shearsman.com/pages/books/catalog/2007/pessoa_engl.html | access-date = 28 July 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110402024401/http://www.shearsman.com/pages/books/catalog/2007/pessoa_engl.html | archive-date = 2 April 2011 | url-status = dead | df = dmy-all }}\n* {{citation | title = Message | others = Jonathan Griffin, transl | place = Exeter, UK | publisher = Shearsman Books | year = 2007 | isbn = 978-1-905700-27-1 | url = http://www.shearsman.com/pages/books/catalog/2007/pessoa_msg.html | access-date = 28 July 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110402022853/http://www.shearsman.com/pages/books/catalog/2007/pessoa_msg.html | archive-date = 2 April 2011 | url-status = dead | df = dmy-all }}\n* ''Selected English Poems '', ed. Tony Frazer, Exeter (UK): Shearsman Books, 2007. {{ISBN|1-905700-26-1}}\n* ''A Centenary Pessoa'', tr. [[Keith Bosley]] & L. C. Taylor, foreword by Octavio Paz, Carcanet Press, 2006. {{ISBN|1-85754-724-1}}\n* ''A Little Larger Than the Entire Universe: Selected Poems'', tr. Richard Zenith, Penguin Classics, 2006. {{ISBN|0-14-303955-5}}\n* ''The Education of the Stoic'', tr. Richard Zenith, afterword by Antonio Tabucchi, Exact Change, 2004. {{ISBN|1-878972-40-5}}\n* ''[[The Book of Disquiet]]'', tr. Richard Zenith, Penguin classics, 2003. {{ISBN|978-0-14-118304-6}}\n* ''The Selected Prose of Fernando Pessoa'', tr. Ric